#software.container
  .row
    .cold-lg
      h2
        i(class="fas fa-wrench")
        |  Software
      p.
        Query and publish RDF datasets using SaGe servers using these client or server implementations.
      .row
        .col
          .card
            center(class="card-img-top")
              i(class="fa-8x fab fa-python")
            .card-body
              h5(class="card-title").
                SaGe server - Python
              .card-text
                p.
                  Publish your own datasets using the reference SaGe implementation in Python.
                  Currently supports RDF datasets stored in <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/">PostgreSQL</a> and in the <a href="http://www.rdfhdt.org/">HDT format</a>.
              a(href="https://github.com/sage-org/sage-engine", class="btn btn-outline-primary")
                i(class="fas fa-download")
                |  Download
              | 
              a(href="https://cloud.docker.com/repository/docker/callidon/sage", class="btn btn-outline-primary")
                i(class="fab fa-docker")
                |  Docker image
        .col  
          .card
            center(class="card-img-top")
              i(class="fa-8x fab fa-java")
            .card-body
              h5(class="card-title").
                SaGe client - Apache Jena
              .card-text
                p.
                  Based on <a href="https://jena.apache.org/">Apache jena</a>, this client supports the full SPARQL 1.1 syntax, including federated SPARQL queries.
              a(href="https://github.com/sage-org/sage-jena/releases", class="btn btn-outline-primary")
                i(class="fas fa-download")
                |  Download
              | 
              a(href="https://github.com/sage-org/sage-jena", class="btn btn-outline-primary")
                i(class="fab fa-github")
                |  See on Github

        .col  
          .card
            center(class="card-img-top")
              i(class="fa-8x fab fa-js")
            .card-body
              h5(class="card-title").
                SaGe client - Javascript
              .card-text
                p.
                  The SaGe javascript client allows you to execute SPARQL 1.1 queries in any browser or using <a href="https://nodejs.org/en/">Node.js</a>.
              a(href="https://github.com/sage-org/sage-client", class="btn btn-outline-primary")
                i(class="fas fa-download")
                |  Download
              | 
              a(href="https://github.com/sage-org/sage-client", class="btn btn-outline-primary")
                i(class="fab fa-github")
                |  See on Github
